    <h2>Advantages of the Hourglass Body Type Diet</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Balanced Nutritional Intake: A varied diet helps maintain muscle tone and a healthy metabolism.</li>
        <li>Support for Curvy Proportions: Focused nutrition can help manage weight while supporting the natural curves of the body.</li>
        <li>Flexibility in Food Choices: Hourglass body types can enjoy a diverse range of foods, which can help prevent feelings of deprivation.</li>
        <li>Muscle Maintenance: Adequate protein intake supports muscle retention, which is crucial for overall metabolism and body composition.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Workout Recommendations for Hourglass Body Type Females</h2>
    <p><strong>Strength Training:</strong> Incorporate resistance exercises 3-4 times a week, focusing on both upper and lower body workouts to enhance muscle definition and maintain curves. Target areas include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Squats and lunges for the lower body</li>
        <li>Push-ups and rows for the upper body</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Cardiovascular Exercise:</strong> Engage in moderate-intensity cardio, such as brisk walking, cycling, or swimming, for at least 150 minutes per week to promote heart health and manage body composition.</p>
    <p><strong>High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT):</strong> Consider incorporating HIIT workouts 1-2 times a week for improved endurance and calorie burning.</p>
    <p><strong>Flexibility and Core Work:</strong> Include yoga or Pilates to enhance flexibility, core strength, and posture.</p>

